{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peVE|AposGlory|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peVE|AposGlory|melody', 'text' : 'Idiomelon.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peVE|AposGlory|text', 'text' : 'O Friend of humanity, great and incomprehensible is the abundance of your tender mercies. You displayed forebearance when You were slapped by Jews, when You were touched by Your Apostle, and as the object of inquiry of those who reject You. How did You become incarnate? How were You, the sinless One, crucified? We pray You grant us understanding, so that like Thomas we may shout to You, "My Lord and my God, glory to You!"'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma11|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma11|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma11|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma12|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma12|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma12|text', 'text' : 'The women went early in the morning to the gravesite, * and when they beheld the appearance of an angel they trembled. * The sepulcher radiated life; the wonder filled them with astonishment. * Hence they went away, proclaiming the resurrection unto the Disciples. * "Christ has despoiled Hades, as the One * mighty and only powerful, * and He raised up all who were corrupted, * and dispelled the fear of condemnation, by the power of the Cross."'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma1T|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma1T|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma1T|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma21|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma21|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Kathisma21|text', 'text' : 'For fear of the Judeans, the Disciples were in hiding,* having congregated in Zion. You came to them, O Good One,* the doors being shut, and You stood* among them, and You caused them to rejoice.* And You showed them the wounds on Your hands* and immaculate side, saying* unto the disbelieving Disciple,* "Put out your hand and examine Me,* for it is I, who for you became passible."'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds1|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds1|text', 'text' : 'O Christ, we praise in song Your saving Passion, and Your resurrection do we glorify.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds2|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds2|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds2|text', 'text' : 'You endured crucifixion and abolished death and resurrected from the dead. Do therefore now bring peace into our life, O Lord, as the only Almighty One.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds3|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds3|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds3|text', 'text' : 'You stripped Hades of plunder, and humanity You resurrected by Your resurrection, O Christ. Do therefore now account us worthy with a pure heart to praise You and glorify.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds4|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds4|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds4|text', 'text' : 'We glorify Your divine condescension, and we sing Your praise, O Christ. You were born of a Virgin, and from the Father You remained inseparable. You suffered as a man and voluntarily endured the Cross. As one emerging from a bridal chamber, You rose from the sepulcher, in order to save the world. Glory to You, O Lord.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|LaudsGlory|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 2.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|LaudsGlory|melody', 'text' : 'Idiomelon.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|LaudsGlory|text', 'text' : 'After eight days from Your resurrection, O Jesus our King, and the Father's only-begotten Word, You appeared to Your Disciples, the doors being shut; and You granted them Your peace. And to the disbelieving Disciple You showed the marks on Your body. "Come and touch my hands and my feet, and my uncorrupt side." And he believed and cried to You, "My Lord and my God, glory to You."'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha1|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha1|text', 'text' : 'O Giver-of-Life, You did not break * the seals that secured Your tomb. * And likewise after Your awesome rising from the sepulcher, * You unhindered entered * the room where Your glorious * Apostles were, the doors being shut, O Christ, and caused them to rejoice. * And You granted them Your governing* Holy Spirit,* for mercy immeasurable.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha2|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha2|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha2|text', 'text' : 'Thomas, who was also called the Twin, * was not there when You appeared * to the Disciples, O Lord, and therefore he did not believe * that You resurrected. * Thus emphatically he cried* aloud to those who saw You, "Unless I put my finger in His side * and the wounds created by the nails, * I will not believe that He indeed arose."'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha3|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha3|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d084_en_US_dedes|peMA|Aposticha3|text', 'text' : '"O Thomas, according to your wish, * handle Me," said Christ to him. * "Put out your hand, and be cognizant that I have flesh and bones, * and an earthen body. * Be not one who disbelieves. * But rather with the others be confident." And he in turn cried out, * "You, O Jesus, are my Lord and God, * and my Savior. * Glory to Your resurrection."'}
